So here Desiree's showing, logging into her existing Netlify account, existing GitHub

00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:47.300
account, GitHub account, all right, thank you.

00:42:47.300 --> 00:42:53.219
And it creates a new repository in her GitHub with the exact same files that I had, and

00:42:53.219 --> 00:42:56.979
it automatically deploys it to Netlify with all the same settings that I had created.

00:42:56.979 --> 00:43:01.179
So now Desiree has her own copy of my exact same site with one button.

00:43:01.179 --> 00:43:06.540
She clicked on the deploy to Netlify button in my repository, her site deploy is in progress.

00:43:07.219 --> 00:43:13.379
It takes a little while for Hugo to build the site, so insert Jeopardy music here while

00:43:13.379 --> 00:43:14.379
it's going.

00:43:14.379 --> 00:43:15.379
There we go.

00:43:15.379 --> 00:43:18.620
Stoic Snyder is now live, so she can click on that.

00:43:18.620 --> 00:43:22.379
So that's the exact same site that I just showed you, but now it's based off source

00:43:22.379 --> 00:43:28.820
files in her GitHub repository deployed to her own URL in Netlify, Stoic Snyder, and

00:43:28.820 --> 00:43:34.659
then she can change that, she can edit the files, and she can employ continuous deployment

00:43:34.780 --> 00:43:39.020
with Netlify, which is by connecting your GitHub account and using GitHub to store your

00:43:39.020 --> 00:43:43.300
source files, you can connect that to Netlify so that every time you make a change and you

00:43:43.300 --> 00:43:47.139
push to GitHub, the website can automatically update.

00:43:47.139 --> 00:43:51.260
So this is how I would really recommend, if you want to use BlogDown, it's one of the

00:43:51.260 --> 00:43:58.580
great benefits without needing to worry too much about remembering to update your site.

00:43:58.580 --> 00:44:02.699
So if you're familiar with Git and GitHub for version control, and you'd like to take

00:44:02.699 --> 00:44:05.580
a foray into BlogDown, I recommend that.

