00:53:20.620 --> 00:53:23.219
All you really need to know is know the output directory, right, Desiree?

00:53:23.219 --> 00:53:27.939
As long as you can drag and drop or place that somewhere, then you've got a hosted website.

00:53:27.939 --> 00:53:28.939
Yeah.

00:53:28.939 --> 00:53:35.419
As soon as I guess, yeah, as soon as you have those HTML files in some place, then you can

00:53:35.540 --> 00:53:40.179
use whatever server you want following the instructions of whatever that server uses.

00:53:40.179 --> 00:53:47.500
But that's why it's really nice to know where the site actually is because it's your source

00:53:47.500 --> 00:53:52.860
files are in your project folder, but knowing where the actual website lives in a directory

00:53:52.860 --> 00:53:58.179
is nice because that's the only folder that you need to be able to share.

00:53:58.179 --> 00:53:59.179
Yes.

